  "prompt": "Why we should study economics?",
  "response": "There are several important reasons to study economics:\n\n1. Understanding Economic Systems\n- Learn how economies function\n- Comprehend market mechanisms\n- Analyze supply and demand dynamics\n\n2. Personal Financial Management\n- Make better personal financial decisions\n- Understand investment strategies\n- Develop financial literacy\n\n3. Career Opportunities\n- Wide range of career paths\n- Applicable in various sectors\n- High-demand professional skills\n\n4. Policy and Decision Making\n- Understand government economic policies\n- Analyze social and economic challenges\n- Develop critical thinking skills\n\n5. Global Perspective\n- Comprehend international trade\n- Understand economic relationships between countries\n- Recognize global economic trends\n\n6. Problem-Solving Skills\n- Develop analytical thinking\n- Learn data interpretation\n- Enhance logical reasoning abilities\n\n7. Social Impact\n- Understand economic inequality\n- Analyze poverty and development\n- Explore solutions to economic challenges\n\n8. Business and Entrepreneurship\n- Learn business strategy\n- Understand market competition\n- Develop economic forecasting skills\n\n9. Personal and Professional Growth\n- Enhance decision-making capabilities\n- Develop quantitative reasoning\n- Improve strategic thinking\n\n10. Adaptability in Changing Economies\n- Understand technological disruptions\n- Recognize economic transformation\n- Prepare for future economic challenges",
